<br>
That said, the problem is not only that the server is too crowded with high end folks, though it sure is that. The game itself has shifted to a majority population of high-enders. One other thing is that guilds have focused for too long on doing planes raids because of the gear that can be gotten. While planes raids are good things to do, I think that repeatedly doing planes raids to 'equip' a guild with planar gear is wasted effort. Why? Becuase there are so many things out there now (and this is pre-Luclin) that are as good if not better than planar gear for a guild. The Plane of Growth armors, the Coldain/Kael quest armors (same as the POG armors mostly), and even the Icewall Keep raid type armors are so much better. Guilds would be better served doing less planar raids and more of these type of things, as well as some of the Luclin stuff. Diversify! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>Haemish MacLennan<br>
